0008|- [HelpText]
0009|*SURVO MM supports graphical operations
0010|S PLOT  on PostScript printers (PS)
S   |  7777
0011|*       and
0012|S GPLOT in the screen graphics.
S   |  77777
0014|*A PostScript printer is ideal for producing plots of high quality and
0015|*for making multipage documents with graphical illustrations (see option
0016|*- picture in PRINT?).
0017|*PostScript files made by Survo can also be printed by means of various
0018|*Windows programs (like GSview and Adobe Acrobat) on any Windows printer.
0020|*Plots on the screen are useful when planning graphical illustrations
0021|*and in interactive graphics.
0022|*Since the screen plots can be saved on the disk as enhanced metafiles, also
0023|*sequences of pictures and overlays of them may be created.
0025|*The PLOT operation and the GPLOT operation are almost
0026|*identical in most applications. When a plotting scheme has to be
0027|*transferred from the screen to printers or plotters or vice versa, it is usually
0028|*question of changing PLOT to GPLOT and adjusting some dimension
0029|*parameters (like SIZE) only.
0030|*Often such adjustments can be avoided by using specification MODE=PS in
0031|*GPLOT plotting schemes.
