0116|- [HelpText]
0117|*The initial logical size of a graphics window is given by the keyword
0118|*'videomode' in the system file SURVO.APU.
0119|*videomode=<width>,<height>  (for example, videomode=1000,1000)
S   |           <     > <      >
0120|*gives the default size of graphics windows in logical units.
0121|*In order to provide compatibility with earlier Survo versions, following
0122|*shorthand notations are available:
0123|*videomode=EGA  is the same as videomode=480,350 .
0124|*Similarly VGA corresponds to 600,480, CGA to 320,200, SVGA to 800,600,
0125|*and XRES to 1024,768.
0126|*To quarantee the best possible compatibility with PostScript graphics
0127|*it is worthwhile to use a new alternative videomode=PS
0128|*where parameters <width> and <height> are chosen according to the SIZE
S   |                  <     >     <      >
0129|*specification. Then also certain other attributes of the graph (like
0130|*font sizes) are transformed in such way that the picture corresponds
0131|*closely to PostScript version of the same plotting scheme.
