0169|+GLAYOUT? þ PRINT CUR+1,E TO q111_07.html
0170|- include HTML40.DEV
0171|- include Q.DV2
0172|- [HelpText]
0173|*The number, sizes and locations of graphics windows are controlled by
0174|*the command
0175|*GPLOT /LAYOUT <text file with .SYS extension>.
S   |               <                             >
0176|*GPLOT /LAYOUT (without parameter)
0177|*lets Windows to position graphics windows automatically. Max. # is 300.
0179|*The default setting of Survo graphics windows is typically
0180|*gplot_layout=SUR_G3.SYS  (given in SURVO.APU).
0181|*These SYS files are located in the subdirectory of SURVO MM containing
0182|*GPLOT modules (in <Survo>\U\G).
S   |                   <     >
0183|*The contents of SUR_G3 is
0184|*3 1024 768          / # of windows and size of the reference screen
0185|*700   0 300 225     / locations and sizes of windows in pixels
0186|*700 250 300 225
0187|*700 500 300 225
0189|*Certain predefined settings can be selected most easily by soft buttons
0190|*SYSTEM -> GRAPH.
S   |         >
0192|*Specifications WHOME=<x>,<y> and WSIZE=<window_width>,<window_height>
S   |                      < > < >           <            > <             >
0193|*always override the current setting permitting a temporary positioning
0194|*of a graphic window irrespective of the current /LAYOUT setting.
0195|*<x> and <y> give the coordinates of the top-left corner of the window
S   | < >     < >
0196|*in the coordinate system where (0,0) is the top-left corner of the screen.
0197|*(This is a Windows OS convention).
0198|*In these specifications, notations WX and WY are permitted giving the
0199|*width and height of the entire screen.
0200|*........................................................................
0201|*For example,
0202|*GPLOT Y(X)=X / WHOME=WX/2,0 WSIZE=WX/2,WY/2
0203|*plots the graph in a window which is in the top right corner of the screen
0204|*and takes one quarter of the total size of the screen.
0205|*........................................................................
0206|*Specifications HOME=<x_home>,<y_home> and SIZE=<plot_size>,<plot_width>
S   |                     <      > <      >          <         > <          >
0207|*give the actual location and size of the graph in logical coordinates.
0208|*HOME=0,0 now refers to the bottom-left corner of the of the current
0209|*graphics window. (This is a normal convention in all reasonable systems.)
