0220|- [HelpText]
0221|*Control commands for Survo graphics windows:
0223|*Each graphics window of SURVO MM can be freely moved, resized, minimized
0224|*maximized, and deleted by the mouse.
0225|*Modifications can be done also by special GPLOT control commands.
0226|*These are useful tools especially when making graphical applications
0227|*of Survo as sucros.
0229|*GPLOT /DEL ALL
0230|*closes all existing SURVO MM graphics windows.
0231|*GPLOT /DEL <integer>
S   |            <       >
0232|*closes the window having the given number in its title bar.
0233|*GPLOT /SHOW MIN <integer>
S   |                 <       >
0234|*minimizes the given Survo graphics window.
0235|*GPLOT /SHOW NORMAL <integer>
S   |                    <       >
0236|*restores the window to its earlier size and position (after /SHOW MIN)
0237|*GPLOT /SHOW MAX <integer>
S   |                 <       >
0238|*maximizes the given Survo graphics window. In sucros use WIN MIN to
0239|*to overlap the main window (edit field) by the picture.
0241|*Control commands for Survo graphics windows: (continued)
0243|*GPLOT /NEXT <integer>
S   |             <       >
0244|*selects the next graphics window to be the one with the order <integer>
S   |                                                               <       >
0245|*in the current layout.
0246|*GPLOT /PREV
0247|*selects the previous graphics window for the next graph. This command
0248|*(with IN- and OUTFILE specifications) provides a simple way for
0249|*making overlay graphics (in sucros).
0250|*GPLOT /FIX <integer>
S   |            <       >
0251|*selects a fixed graphics window with order <integer> for all subsequent graphs.
S   |                                            <       >
0252|*This command is helpful in the same way as GPLOT /PREV.
0253|*GPLOT /DEL ALL and GPLOT /NEXT <integer> commands cancel the /FIX setting.
S   |                                <       >
0254|*GPLOT /WHICH
0255|*tells the number of the next graphics window to be used by typing that
0256|*number after the command. Again useful feature in sucros and in connection
0257|*with GPLOT /FIX <integer>, for example.
S   |                 <       >
0259|*GPLOT /FIRST <integer>
S   |              <       >
0260|*limits rotation of graphics windows. For example, if # of windows
0261|*(according the current layout) is 8 and GPLOT /FIRST 5 is activated,
0262|*the windows of subsequent GPLOT's will be rotating according to sequence
0263|*5,6,7,8,5,6,7,8,5,6,7,8,... thus leaving windows 1,2,3,4 intact.
